Thanks so much,<br>
Rosey</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.processVote?topicID=734.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Defense</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Offense</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Group enhancing benefits</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>RAs</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="5"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Other</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"></form><a HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessage?topicID=734.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 12:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing . . .</span><hr size=1> I voted for Group Enhancing benefits.  Overall our defense stinks but the additions to HP makes it a bit better (if ranking I would make this 2).  Offense is where it should be now.  RA’s, although they NEED a lot of work, are not going to be addressed until the general RA review.  <br>
<br>
I still want to see a second Skald chant for combat, slight in crease in our Damage add song (Level 50 should be the equivalent of Level 50 Minstrel Ablative or basically +70 per swing) and a combining of the resist chats ala the Paladins advance resist chant.  <br>
<br>
Just my opinion.<br>
<br>
P.S. Rosey, THANKS for all the hard work up to now.  The changes of 1.65 were wonderful and I don’t think we would have gotten anything without your leadership. <br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A> at: 10/13/03 12:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drioz>Drioz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing . . .</span><hr size=1> I personally want more group effective chants, but sonething uniquie, like minsterls havd ablative, and bard with with CC albilities, skalds should have more offensive chatd, and i mena more that just  a DA, even if the DPS was increasedm i personally would want something more, like a haste that stacks with celerity, or a group ewffective damage shield that worth a darn <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clapperoth>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 2:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing . . .</span><hr size=1> I voted defence mostly because I feel it balances the 1.65 effects more.  We are now a more efficient damage dealing class, which makes us more of a target in group RvR.  Personally I've never really wanted a lot more damage dealing ability, I've wanted the ability to survive better and last longer. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg<br>
Guild Officer<br>
Rune<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isenheart>Isenheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.richardsimmons.com/images/img/RichardBiofotos1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 2:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing . . .</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;I still want to see a second Skald chant for combat, slight in crease in our Damage add song (Level 50 should be the equivalent of Level 50 Minstrel Ablative or basically +70 per swing) and a combining of the resist chats ala the Paladins advance resist chant&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
the paladin's combined resist chants drain power.  are you sure you want that? <p>------------------<br>
Isenheart - 50 Paladin R3L6<br>
Avidius - 50 Paladin R4L6<br>
Troublemaker - 50 Shadowblade R5L2<br>
Shaymus - 50 Cabalist R3L2<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 2:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing . . .</span><hr size=1> Actually yeah I do.  As the resist chants are now they are very situational.  If we had the advanced chant it would allow us to use the single line one if that was needed or go for the broad one that sucks power.  Would I miss the power for me DDs?  Sure but I would also have a reason to have 2 skalds in the group and more flexibility to help where I could.  I also think this is more realistic as Mythic, with its new TL coordinator, looks like they are not longer adding things to classes.  Just modifying existing abilities and bringing them up, or down, to a level.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gin@teamskald>Gin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 4:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The next thing</span><hr size=1> I voted for adding another group ability.  I would like to see some kind of added benefit for taking battlesongs to 50, and having more than one skald in a group.  <br>
<br>
I really feel like our RA needs to be changed also.  After the last patch, I find our offense to be ok, and defense is where it should be since we trade something for our utility and offense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 432<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/03 4:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next thing</span><hr size=1> I don't want anyone to misunderstand.  Just because something has been decided to work on, doesn't mean the other things will be ignored.  One step at a time would seem to be the best way to go.  If we can focus on the issues of one area, then provide the best data we can and get it reviewed, and evaluate the changes if we get any and see how the class works, then we can move to another thing.<br>
<br>
I know I put RAs up there as a choice, but with the coming RA review, it really shouldn't be on this list.  I will be pushing hard for a change to the unique RA and the availability of other RAs regardless of the outcome of this poll.<br>
<br>
Spread the word on the poll if you would, the more Skalds that answer, the better focused we can be.<br>
<br>
